<h2>RESPONSIBILITIES/ROLES</h2>
<ol>
<li>Provide in-person and telephone assistance (information and guidance) to parents regarding special education procedures for school-age children with disabilities, with major emphasis on early childhood special education.</li>
   <li>Co-present and present workshops in communities for parents of young children with disabilities and professionals who provide services.</li>
   <li>Assist in public information and education activities with presentations to various organizations and professional groups.</li>
   <li>Assist in data collection for evaluation reports and other diverse tasks.</li>
   <li>Write informative handouts and material on early childhood and related topics.</li>
   <li>Other activities as required.
</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2>EXPERIENCE/BACKGROUND SKILLS</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Ability to work well with others, and interest in relating to parents of children birth to 5 with disabilities.</li>
   <li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or related experience in Early Childhood Special Education.</li>
   <li>Experience or willingness to learn more about public speaking, workshop presentations, and assisting others on the telephone.</li>
   <li>Experience working with parents of young children and professionals and early childhood special education.</li>
   <li>Knowledge of laws and rules related to the education of early childhood and school-age children with disabilities.</li>
   <li>Ability to keep good records and collect data for evaluation purposes.</li>
   <li>Ability to provide own transportation and flexibility to travel. Workshops are presented during both day time and evening hours, therefore, flexible schedule needed.</li>
   <li>Experience in community service/human service/social service.</li>
   <li>Ability to work with diverse populations.</li>
   <li>Ability to apply analytical skills.</li>
   <li>Excellent organizational skills, ability to meet deadlines.</li>
   <li>Sensitivity to and knowledge of cultural competence related to a variety of cultures.</li>
   <li>College degree or equivalent background gained through training or work experience.
  </li>
</ol>
<hr />
<p><strong>Salary to be determined  based on experience.</strong></p>
<p>  Position available  immediately.</p>
<p>  Parents of children with  disabilities are encouraged to apply.</p>
